ShadowQuest

Class PassiveMonster

  • java.lang.Object
    • ShadowQuest.GameObject
      • ShadowQuest.Unit
        • ShadowQuest.Monster
          • ShadowQuest.PassiveMonster

  • public class PassiveMonster
extends Monster
    Passive monsters wander around the map randomly by default. After a set time interval, the monster will choose and move in one of 9 directions. If the passive monster is attacked it will flee from the attacking unit for a set time period, before resuming its default wandering behaviour. Passive monsters cannot attack.
    Author:
    Adrian Cheung
